Dear speakers
Thank you for your talks at YAPC::Asia Tokyo 2013

The festivities are over, but if you haven't done so, we'd much appreciate you writing a blog entry about it. Also, please take a few minutes to answer our questionnaire:

Finally, there are two important things we'd like you to check about your talk:

    http://yapcasia.org/2013/talk/show/[% talk.id %]

1) Please upload your slides
    For each talk page on the YAPC::Asia site, you can register your slides.
    If it's an embeddable slide like slideshare, we embed it right on the
    page for easy viewing.
    You can register your slide url by following the "edit talk" link.

2) Please check photo/video permissions
    This year we included a way in the talk submission form to speficy
    if you allow photos of you being taken + if you allow video of your
    talk being recorded. However, it seems like somewhere along the way
    we messed up and the default value was "disallow".
    We naturally would like to make as many photos and videos public,
    and would like to ask you to check your talks and make sure that
    the permissions are as you expect.

